But we should take with reserve the statement of Altenanus (A 9) that, after 1536, Goelenius had frequently spoken and sometimes acted as though 110 recognized no trust, but was free to use Erasmus' menies as he would. Altenanus speaks of being able to produce witnesses to this effect; but it is not clear that they could have borne cross-examination.

Ep. 2863 and the Memorandum embodied in ΑΖ are seen in their proper light when compared with the two Memoranda printed in Ep. 2855 introd., which record deposits made by Erasmus with Amerbach. The first of those two Memoranda was drawn up on 13 Aug. 1533 (fifteen days before Ep. 2863 was written). Dissatisfied with the form of it Erasmus drew up an amended Memorandum on 8 April 1534: on the same day, that is, as that on which (dissatisfied with the form of Ep. 2803) he amended the record of deposits with Goclenius to the form seen in A 2.
